{"file_path": "/workspace/output/development-agreement-draft.md", "new_string": "[Drafting Note — Conflict C2 (36-month clock). Resolution Condition #8(h) measures the 36-month period from the date of conveyance. Section 14.2(a) instead measures the completion obligation against the Phase I Substantial Completion deadline of September 30, 2028 (as extended by Force Majeure and Construction Lender extensions), which is tied to the March 1, 2026 groundbreaking. This avoids the timing mismatch under which a 36-month-from-conveyance clock could expire before the Substantial Completion deadline. The City should confirm acceptance of measuring the completion assurance against the Substantial Completion deadline rather than a fixed 36-month-from-conveyance period.]

[Drafting Note — Conflict C45 (Resolution "net of damages" refund vs. alternative repurchase price). Resolution Condition #8(h) provides that, upon reversion, the City's obligation is to refund to Developer the purchase price paid "net of any damages incurred by the City as a result of the Developer's failure to timely complete Phase I." The alternative repurchase option in Section 14.2(c) instead sets the repurchase price at the lesser of the original purchase price ($9,200,000) or then-current fair market value (by MAI appraisal), and does not include a "net of damages" deduction. These mechanisms differ: the Resolution's "net of damages" concept allows the City to offset its actual damages against the refund, while Section 14.2(c)'s "lesser of purchase price or FMV" could result in a repurchase price below the original purchase price if the Property's value has declined, but does not separately deduct the City's damages. If the City wishes to preserve a damages offset within the alternative mechanism, the parties should negotiate whether the City's actual damages (above the performance security drawn under Section 14.2(d)) may be offset against the repurchase price, subject to a cap and the Construction Lender's mortgage priority. This is an open item; Developer's position is that the $15,000,000 performance security (Section 14.2(d)) is the City's primary financial remedy and that the repurchase price should not be further reduced by a discretionary damages offset.]

[Drafting Note — Conflict C46 (loan default on imposition of lien/reversion). The Loan Term Sheet (Section 9(11)) provides that the "imposition, creation, or recording of any lien, encumbrance, or interest upon the Project site without Lender's prior written consent, including without limitation any reversionary interest, right of re-entry, possibility of reverter, or defeasible condition in favor of the City of Lakemont or any other party," constitutes an Event of Default under the Construction Loan. This is a distinct loan-default trigger that reinforces the prohibition in Article 14 and Section 4.4: even if the City were to record a reversionary interest (contrary to this Agreement), the act of recording would simultaneously default the Construction Loan. This underscores that no reversionary interest may be recorded against the Property. The Resolution (Condition #8(h)) contemplates that the reversionary interest "shall be recorded against the Property at the time of conveyance"; Section 4.4 and Article 14 prohibit any such recording, and the City must agree that no reversionary interest will be recorded.]", "old_string": "[Drafting Note — Conflict C2 (36-month clock). Resolution Condition #8(h) measures the 36-month period from the date of conveyance. Section 14.2(a) instead measures the completion obligation against the Phase I Substantial Completion deadline of September 30, 2028 (as extended by Force Majeure and Construction Lender extensions), which is tied to the March 1, 2026 groundbreaking. This avoids the timing mismatch under which a 36-month-from-conveyance clock could expire before the Substantial Completion deadline. The City should confirm acceptance of measuring the completion assurance against the Substantial Completion deadline rather than a fixed 36-month-from-conveyance period.]"}

